TITLE: Basic Usage of useUnistyles Hook in React Native
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to import and use the useUnistyles hook to access theme and runtime properties in a React Native component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jpudysz/react-native-unistyles/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/v3/references/use-unistyles.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useUnistyles } from 'react-native-unistyles'

const MyComponent = () => {
    const { theme, rt } = useUnistyles()

    return (
        // your view
    )
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using Variants as Component Props in React Native Unistyles
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use variants as component props, including TypeScript type definitions for the props.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jpudysz/react-native-unistyles/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/v3/references/variants.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React from 'react'
import { StyleSheet } from 'react-native-unistyles'

type ComponentProps = {
    color: 'primary' | 'secondary'
    size: 'small' | 'medium' | 'large'
}

const Component: React.FunctionComponent = ({ color, size }) => {
    styles.useVariants({
        color,
        size
    })

    return (
        <View style={styles.container} />
    )
}
```

