TITLE: Defining Basic Variant Structure in React Native Unistyles
DESCRIPTION: Shows the basic structure for defining variants within a StyleSheet.create call in Unistyles. Variants are nested objects within style definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jpudysz/react-native-unistyles/blob/main/docs/src/content/docs/v3/references/variants.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const styles = StyleSheet.create(theme => ({
    container: {
        backgroundColor: theme.colors.background,
        variants: {
            // here you can define your variants
        }
    },
    text: {
        color: theme.colors.text,
        variants: {
            // here you can define other variants!
        }
    }
}))
```

